    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Characteristic ‘ice-cream’ pink in colour and forming dense cushions of short, closely-packed upright axes, each of which bears tapering lateral branchlets, much like a pine-tree. Tips of branches acute.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_7601",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Short, reaching only about 20 mm in height, branches about 1 mm in diameter.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_7602",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Primarily a tropical species widespread in Indian Ocean and western Pacific.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u><i> </i>Previous distribution given as KwaZulu-Natal to Algoa Bay but the photographed specimens were seem in Muizenberg, extending the distribution to False Bay.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_7603",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>In more tropical areas can form carpets in low intertidal pools and on shallow reefs, but in False Bay found growing commonly on margins of mussels (<i>Choromytilus meridionalis</i>) in a low intertidal pool. Produced a potent neurotoxin, demoic acid, that is usually associated with toxic phytoplankton blooms and which causes amnesic shellfish poisoning.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_7604",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Photosynthetic.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_7605",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>Tetraspores borne in terminal branchlets.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_7606",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>Unlikely to be mistaken for any other species, due to unusual pink colour and short, closely-packed cushions with distinctive branching pattern.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_7607",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
